body:
The `languageOptions.ecmaVersion` value is not respected at all, it doesn't matter if it's `2023` or `'latest'`, it's simply not cared about.

Only `parserOptions.ecmaVersion` is respected by the rules currently, i.e. e.g.: https://github.com/eslint/eslint/blob/main/lib/rules/comma-dangle.js#L137

```
    create(context) {
        const options = normalizeOptions(context.options[0], context.parserOptions.ecmaVersion);
```
